voting application
WHAT ???
A functionality where user can give vote to the given set of candidates

Models?
Routes?

voting app functionality
1. user signs in/signs up
2. see the list of candidates
3. give vote to one of the candidate, after giving vote user cannot give vote again
4. there is a route which shows the list of candidates and their live vote counts sorted by their vote count 
5. user data must contain their one unique government id proof named: aadhar card number
6. there should be one admin who can only maintain the table of candidates and he can't able to vote at all
7. user can change their password
8. user can login only with aadhar card number and password
9. admin can't vote at all

% 6. user can only give vote if their aadhar card number is valid (12 digit number)
% 7. user can only give vote if their aadhar card number is not already used for voting


------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Routes:

User Authentication:
- POST /signup: - Register a new user with aadhar card number and password.
- POST /login: - Log in to an existing account (aadhar card number + password).

Voting:
- GET /electors: - Retrieve the list of candidates with their current vote counts.
- POST /vote/:electorId: - Submit a vote for a candidate (spacific candidate).

Vote Counts:
- GET /vote/counts: - Get the list of candidates sorted by their vote counts.

User Profile:
- GET /profile: - Get user profile information (excluding sensitive data).
- PUT /profile/change-password: - Change the user's password.

Admin candidate Management:
- POST /admin/candidates: - Add a new candidate (admin only).
- PUT /admin/candidates/:candidateId: - Update candidate information (admin only).
- DELETE /admin/candidates/:candidateId: - Remove a candidate (admin only).